                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Rāmachandraperumāḷ temple.</p>						                            
                            <p>Achutadēva-mahārāya. 1544 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The details of date, <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi> Śaka 1466, Krōdhin, Makara śu. 12, Thursday, Rōhiṇī, correspond to 1544 A.D., December 25, Thursday, f.d.n. ·07.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription records that the village Teṉṉāṟampaṭṭu <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rāmachandrapuram, which had been granted as <hi rend="italic">tiruviḍaiyāṭṭam</hi> by Mallappa-nāyaka of Vēppanpaṭṭu was reendowed for <hi rend="italic">Sarvādhyayana</hi> by the authorities of the Rāmachandra-perumāḷ temple at Neḍuṅguṉṟam and Mallappa-nāyaka was to maintain 12 <hi rend="italic">Śrīvaishṇavas</hi> taking part in the <hi rend="italic">tiruvadhyayana.</hi></p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
